<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
    <title>Indian Cuisine</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        header {
            background-color: #f4e1d2;
            padding: 15px;
            border-radius: 8px;
        }

        nav ul {
            list-style-type: none;
            padding: 0;
        }

        nav ul li {
            display: inline;
            margin-right: 15px;
        }

        nav ul li a {
            text-decoration: none;
            font-weight: bold;
            color: darkred;
        }

        figure {
            margin: 20px 0;
        }

        figcaption {
            padding: 10px;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }

        /* 🎨 Cuisine-specific themes */
        .bengali h2 {
            color: #e67e22;
        }

        /* Orange */
        .bengali figcaption {
            background-color: #fdebd0;
            border-left: 4px solid #e67e22;
        }

        .gujarati h2 {
            color: #27ae60;
        }

        /* Green */
        .gujarati figcaption {
            background-color: #eafaf1;
            border-left: 4px solid #27ae60;
        }

        .mughlai h2 {
            color: #8e44ad;
        }

        /* Royal Purple */
        .mughlai figcaption {
            background-color: #f5eaf7;
            border-left: 4px solid #8e44ad;
        }

        .punjabi h2 {
            color: #d4ac0d;
        }

        /* Golden Yellow */
        .punjabi figcaption {
            background-color: #fef9e7;
            border-left: 4px solid #d4ac0d;
        }

        .southindian h2 {
            color: #2980b9;
        }

        /* Deep Blue */
        .southindian figcaption {
            background-color: #ebf5fb;
            border-left: 4px solid #2980b9;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <h1>Indian Cuisine</h1>
    <p>The traditional food of India has been widely appreciated for its fabulous use of herbs and spices...</p>

    <header>
        <h2>Navigational Links</h2>
        <nav>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="#BengaliFood">Bengali</a></li>
                <li><a href="#GujaratiFood">Gujarati</a></li>
                <li><a href="#MughlaiFood">Mughlai</a></li>
                <li><a href="#PunjabiFood">Punjabi</a></li>
                <li><a href="#SouthIndianFood">South Indian</a></li>
            </ul>
        </nav>
    </header>

    <section class="bengali">
        <h2 id="BengaliFood">Bengali Food</h2>
        <figure>
            <img src="https://www.awesomecuisine.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Bengali-Cuisine.jpg" width="300"
                height="250">
            <figcaption>Bengali cuisine is appreciated for its use of panchphoron, a blend of five essential spices...
            </figcaption>
        </figure>
    </section>

    <section class="gujarati">
        <h2 id="GujaratiFood">Gujarati Food</h2>
        <figure>
            <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5c6df920d74562c46b234f9e/1587328696559-W520QMT84BQ7F0GIVO91/thaalsite.jpg"
                width="300" height="250">
            <figcaption>Gujarati food is primarily vegetarian and highly nutritious...</figcaption>
        </figure>
    </section>

    <section class="mughlai">
        <h2 id="MughlaiFood">Mughlai Food</h2>
        <figure>
            <img src="https://static.toiimg.com/thumb/msid-82428481,width-748,height-499,resizemode=4,imgsize-1061969/Most-loved-Mughlai-dishes-one-must-try-in-India.jpg"
                width="300" height="250">
            <figcaption>Mughlai cuisine originates from the Mughal Empire and includes dishes prepared in royal
                kitchens...</figcaption>
        </figure>
    </section>

    <section class="punjabi">
        <h2 id="PunjabiFood">Punjabi Food</h2>
        <figure>
            <img src="https://www.nehascookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/Punjabi-thali-WS.jpg" width="350"
                height="250">
            <figcaption>Punjabi cuisine includes a wide range of vegetarian and non-vegetarian dishes...</figcaption>
        </figure>
    </section>

    <section class="southindian">
        <h2 id="SouthIndianFood">South Indian Food</h2>
        <figure>
            <img src="https://sukhis.com/app/uploads/2022/04/image3-4.jpg" width="350" height="250">
            <figcaption>South Indian cuisine encompasses the food of Tamil Nadu, Andhra Pradesh, Karnataka, Kerala, and
                Telangana...</figcaption>
        </figure>
    </section>
</body>

</html>

